    Don't infer implicits from non-accessible companion (#25367)
    
    Implicits found in the companion object of a type should not be inferred
    if the companion object is not accessible.
    
    Fixes https://github.com/scala/scala3/issues/25347
    
    ## How much have your relied on LLM-based tools in this contribution?
    
    Asked it to forward-port https://github.com/scala/scala/pull/11215, but
    its attempt to fix it was in the wrong spot. So the fix is manual, I
    used the unit test file it created.
    
    ## How was the solution tested?
    
    The test passes, we now get a type mismatch error instead of the
    non-accessible implicit being inferred.
    
    I tried separate compilation with two `scalac` calls in sbt, but that
    did something strange, I ran into a different problem.
    
    I tried `scala3-bootstrapped/publishLocal` to test it but that failed
    too with
    
    ```
    [error] -- [E038] Declaration Error: /Users/luc/code/scala/scala3/library/src/scala/collection/mutable/AnyRefMap.scala:406:15
    [error] 406 |  override def + [V1 >: V](elem1: (K, V1), elem2: (K, V1), elems: (K, V1)*): AnyRefMap[K, V1]^{} = {
    [error]     |               ^
    [error]     |    method + has a different signature than the overridden declaration
    [error]     |
    [error]     | longer explanation available when compiling with `-explain`
    ```
    
    I feel a bit out of time to look further into this right now.

